nt backgrounds. This volume explores the strained reception of these migrants, arguing that this is less a product of racism and xenophobia than of anxiety about social class and the loss of a sense of community that reigned before.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Nov 2022) 0aMiddle classzFrancezGonessexSocial conditions. 0aMiddle classzFrancezGonesse. 0aSuburban lifezFrancezGonesse. 0aSuburbszFrancezGonesse. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Sociology / Urban.2bisacsh1 aCoutant, Isabelle, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aMasclet, Olivier, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBerghahn Books Complete eBook-Package 2016z978311099822140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781785332296?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781785332296423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781785332296/original  a978-3-11-099822-1  Berghahn Books Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK